Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @butternut squash{1}(halved and seeds scooped out), halve lengthways, then scoop out the seeds (peel first if you prefer). Cut into 2cm chunks.

Pop the diced butternut onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary. When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and cooked through, about 25-30 minutes. Turn halfway through.

While the butternut roasts, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the linguine.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and sliced). Cut the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} in half widthways. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly tear the @Serrano ham{6%slices} into large pieces.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @linguine{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, about ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, reserve some of the pasta water, then drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While your pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

When hot, lay the Serrano ham in the frying pan and fry until crisp, about ~{2-3%minutes} each side, then transfer to a #plate{} covered in #kitchen paper{} and set aside.

Add a drizzle more @oil{} to the frying pan, then add the onion. Stir-fry until softened, about ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the broccoli and stir-fry for about ~{2-3%minutes}, then add a splash of @water{}. Pop a #lid{} on the frying pan or cover in #foil{} and cook until tender, another ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the broccoli is tender, remove the lid, stir in the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Pour the @reserved pasta water{125%ml} and @chicken stock paste{10%g} into the frying pan, then stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and Serrano ham. Bring to the boil, then remove from the heat.

Add the cooked pasta and roasted butternut to the sauce.

Taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of @water{} if it's a little thick.

Toss gently to coat, then serve your linguine in large #bowls{}.

Enjoy!